\begin_layout Standard
NetCDF4 supports the compression for variables.
 The default compresison level is defined in the ConfigConstants file.
 The valid range is between 0 and 9.
 The compression level 0 disables the compression.
 Lower number is faster and higher number is better compression.
 Some tools can override this by using tool specific configuration file.
 Indivisual user has an option to override the compression level with the
 environment variable MET_NC_COMPRESS or with the command line argument
 
\begin_inset Quotes eld
\end_inset

-compress level
\begin_inset Quotes erd
\end_inset

.
 THe command line argument has the precedence over the environment variable
 MET_NC_COMPRESS.
\end_layout

